<TITLE> SC upholds Abbas bail, Pankaj gets bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 11 (bdnews24.com)  The Supreme Court has upheld the High Court bail order for former minister Mirza Abbas in a murder case. Appellate chamber judge MA Matin Tuesday set aside a state appeal to stay the High Court's bail order. A High Court bench granted bail on Nov 5 to Abbas accused in the Ejaj murder case which was filed by father of the deceased Azizul Haque of Shahjahanpur on Aug 28 in 2006. Mirza was arrested on March 1 last year. Meanwhile a HC bench of Justice Mohammad Mozammel Hossain and Justice Afzal hossain granted anticipatory bail to Shechchashebak League general secretary Pankaj Devnath in a case of illegal wealth. The lower court on Aug 20 sentenced him to 13 years in jail in the case, filed by the Anticorruption Commission on March 22 this year. bdnew
